{"id":411834,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caroline_Aigle","text":"=\"preserve\">Caroline Aigle (12 September 1974 \u2013 21 August 2007) was a French fighter jet pilot. She was born in Montauban. She was the first in France trained to fly a Mirage 2000. She died of a withering melanoma. She was mother of two boys. President of the French Republic Nicolas Sarkozy awarded her the Medal of Aeronautics by posthumous recognition.\nA few weeks before her death, she was selected by the European Space Agency for training to be an astronaut.\nCaroline Aigle graduates \"\u00C9cole Polytechnique\" and \"\u00C9cole de l'Air\".","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"France","surface_form":"French","offset":70},{"uri":"Fighter_aircraft","surface_form":"fighter","offset":77},{"uri":"Jet_aircraft","surface_form":"jet","offset":85},{"uri":"Pilot","surface_form":"pilot","offset":89},{"uri":"Montauban","surface_form":"Montauban","offset":112},{"uri":"Training","surface_form":"trained","offset":151},{"uri":"Dassault_Mirage_2000","surface_form":"Mirage 2000","offset":168},{"uri":"Melanoma","surface_form":"melanoma","offset":205},{"uri":"Boy","surface_form":"boy","offset":237},{"uri":"President_of_the_French_Republic","surface_form":"President of the French Republic","offset":243},{"uri":"Nicolas_Sarkozy","surface_form":"Nicolas Sarkozy","offset":276},{"uri":"Medal_of_Aeronautics","surface_form":"Medal of Aeronautics","offset":308},{"uri":"Posthumous_recognition","surface_form":"posthumous recognition","offset":332},{"uri":"Week","surface_form":"weeks","offset":362},{"uri":"European_Space_Agency","surface_form":"European Space Agency","offset":410},{"uri":"Astronaut","surface_form":"astronaut","offset":454},{"uri":"%C3%89cole_Polytechnique","surface_form":"\u00C9cole Polytechnique","offset":491},{"uri":"%C3%89cole_de_l%27Air","surface_form":"\u00C9cole de l'Air","offset":517}]}